      "body": "tACK 4b6a842c28010a00e121fd36cc0b4e1fa658d249 on Ubuntu 24.04\r\n\r\nWas able to successfully test that `util_test_runner` and `util_rpcauth_test` are correctly disabled when Python3 interpreter is not found (screenshots below)\r\n\r\nOverally this is an improvement, using the `Python3::Interpreter` target defined directly by find_package(...) is cleaner than relying on the `${PYTHON_COMMAND}` variable we define\r\n\r\nwithout Python3\r\n![Screenshot from 2024-11-19 15-24-13](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e1340c82-2c6b-4bf8-b922-d7374537dca8)\r\n\r\nWith Python3\r\n![Screenshot from 2024-11-19 15-26-39](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/322f6742-1d8e-4e49-8c84-ffb89d745d26)\r\n\r\n",
